SA Weather Service forecaster Bransby Bulo said warm to hot weather will be experienced in Gauteng on Monday and Tuesday. Temperatures are expected to reach between 30 C and 34 C on both days. A heat wave is possible from Wednesday into the weekend for the Gauteng area. Temperatures will be between 34 and 35 in Pretoria Johannesburg and Vereeniging. Under those conditions our advice is that people must try not do hard labour. They must stay hydrated and stay indoors if possible Bulo said.Mpumalanga and KwaZulu Natal will also experience hot weather conditions with a 30 % chance of thunder showers. TMG Digital